[Student "S"]
{When NORTH makes a slam try with a jump to 3\S, the best approach for SOUTH is to agree on 
the trump suit immediately but indicate a minimum hand by bidding 4\S. 

NORTH's next move is logical; RKCB 4NT.

SOUTH shows zero or three Key Cards, and since it could not possibly be zero, NORTH knows they are 
the \SK and both red Aces. Even possessing all the Key Cards NORTH knows there aren't 
enough points for a Grand slam.}

